HEADWORD: pyroxylin
<hw>py*rox"y*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A substance resembling gun cotton in composition and properties,
but distinct in that it is more highly nitrified and is soluble in
alcohol, ether, etc.; -- called also
<altname>pyroxyle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrrhic</ent>⟦br⟧
